-Venomss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufricka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fricka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thesafehouse.org/~fricka/shanks/teenyknot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/01 6:10:44 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/~fricka/sig/5fricka60x56.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OOR heelur</span><hr size=1> Yes it's allowed, game mechanics-wise, on Tallon Zek and Vallon Zek.  And is only upheld by player made &quot;rules&quot;. Vallon Zek was once hinted to be up for hardcoding but nothing came of it and they opened Sullon Zek, which *is* hardcoded.<br>
<br>
